    <p> When I got up in the morning after a hot night the sun was already outside and the clouds were largely disappearing. The night was hot because I had set the heating too high and too lazy to turn it down at night. </p>
    <p> As I said, the morning was nice and cool, at least outside of my motorhome. I took a few more souvenir photos before we took care of the cars. We let off dirty water and replenished clean water. Since we did something like that for the first time, it took a little longer. So we started very late. </p>
    <p> We had looked for two possible routes for Greymouth for the day. The first would be a good bit longer, but it didn't seem as exhausting as the second route. The second would be a good bit shorter but very curvy along the coast and probably also the nicer one. Before we had to decide, we had to drive 100km to the fork. Once there, we quickly decided to take the more strenuous but more beautiful route via Westport. </p>
