    <p> In Westport we only quickly went to the tourist information that we told that we shouldn't dawdle for so long if we wanted to experience the blowholes on the Pancake Rocks live and in action, as they are only really fun with certain tides and wind directions. </p>
    <p> So we only fueled up quickly because there is no tank on the next 100km. The route to the Pancake Rocks is curvy but beautiful. You would actually like to stop, in the middle of the most dangerous curves, just stop and enjoy the sight of the rainforest and the coast around you. We drove through tropical rainforest there. The trees and palm trees are not as high as I had imagined, but the density of the forest and the biodiversity is simply the bare madness. </p>
